OL,3,CValdo Calocane's brother thought
OL,4,Cviolent messages were about suicide
OL,6,FTriple killer Valdo Calocane sent his
OL,7,Fbrother messages about hurting
OL,8,F"permanently", but his brother said he
OL,9,Fthought he was talking about killing
OL,10,Fhimself.
OL,12,FCalocane also told his brother Elias
OL,13,Fhe was "thinking about red rum", which
OL,14,Fis murder spelt backwards.
OL,16,FBut Elias told the Nottingham Attacks
OL,17,FInquiry his brother was a "calm and
OL,18,Fpeaceful" person.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/11
