FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778875555
OL,3,CValdo Calocane's brother thought
OL,4,Cviolent messages were about suicide
OL,6,FFormer student Calocane, who has
OL,7,Fparanoid schizophrenia, stabbed to
OL,8,Fdeath undergraduates Barnaby Webber
OL,9,Fand Grace O'Malley-Kumar, both 19, and
OL,10,Fcaretaker Ian Coates, 65. He then
OL,11,Ftried to murder three pedestrians with
OL,12,Fa van in Nottingham in June 2023.
OL,14,FElias was questioned about text
OL,15,Fmessages sent by the killer in 2020.
OL,17,FHe told the inquiry he thought an "I
OL,18,Flove you" message sent from his
OL,19,Fbrother in January of that year was a
OL,20,F"goodbye message".
OL,26,@yD@cOUzD@IO]|D@AOU|D@QO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778875555
OL,3,CValdo Calocane's brother thought
OL,4,Cviolent messages were about suicide
OL,6,FCalocane, who believed he was being
OL,7,Fmonitored, sent further messages
OL,8,Fsaying "that previous night I felt
OL,9,Fimmense anguish, paranoia, anger,
OL,10,Fhatred" and that he had the "darkest
OL,11,Fthoughts".
OL,13,FAnother message said he "wanted to
OL,14,Fhurt... permanently...", the inquiry
OL,15,Fheard.
OL,17,FElias Calocane said: "I thought he was
OL,18,Ftalking about how he wanted to kill
OL,19,Fhimself the night before."
OL,26,@pD@HOUrD@GO]rD@]OUsD@IO]uD@YOUvD@WO]yD@
OL,26,AVOU{D@ZO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778875555
OL,3,CValdo Calocane's brother thought
OL,4,Cviolent messages were about suicide
OL,6,FRachel Langdale KC, counsel to the
OL,7,Finquiry asked: "He didn't say hurt
OL,8,Fhimself, did he? He just says hurt
OL,9,Fpermanently."
OL,11,FElias Calocane replied: "If you take
OL,12,Fthe messages around it, there's no
OL,13,Fother subject other than Valdo, right?
OL,15,F"He's talking about the situation, the
OL,16,Fmonitoring thing, feeling immense
OL,17,Fanguish and talking about it being
OL,18,Foverwhelming."
OL,26,@oD@POUqD@MO]sD@YOUwD@AOUzD@NO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778875555
OL,3,CValdo Calocane's brother thought
OL,4,Cviolent messages were about suicide
OL,6,FHe added: "I guess maybe it's
OL,7,Fdifficult for people to read these
OL,8,F(text messages) now without the
OL,9,Fcontext of what happened on the 13th
OL,10,Fof June and I completely understand
OL,11,Fthat.
OL,13,F"At this point, Valdo had never been
OL,14,Fviolent at all to anyone. He was a
OL,15,Fvery calm and peaceful person as far
OL,16,Fas I can remember."
OL,18,FIn another message, Calocane told his
OL,19,Fbrother he was "thinking about red rum
OL,20,Fnot 120 minutes ago".
OL,26,@nD@KOUuD@AOUxD@SO]{D@POU|D@TO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/11
